 Tula|Arsenal Tula]]                           | caps11 = 41 | goals11 =  6\n| years12 = 2015      | clubs12 = [[FC Arsenal-2 Tula|Arsenal-2 Tula]]                       | caps12 = 10 | goals12 =  1\n| years13 = 2016      | clubs13 = [[FC Arsenal Tula|Arsenal Tula]]                           | caps13 = 10 | goals13 =  0\n| pcupdate = 22 August 2016\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''Dmitry Alexandrovich Smirnov''' ({{lang-ru|\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043c\u0438\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0432}}; born 13 August 1980 in [[Moscow]]) is a [[Russia]]n footballer.\n\n==Career==\nHe holds the record for [[FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok|Luch]] for most league goals in a year (19 goals in 2005) and left on 7 January 2009 the club and moved to [[FC Terek Grozny]][http://www.transfermarketweb.com/?action=read&idsel=29729].\n\n==Personal==\nHis father, [[Aleksandr Mikhailovich Smirnov|Aleksandr Smirnov]], played in the [[Soviet Top League]] for [[FC Spartak Moscow]].\n\n==Characteristics==\nHe is not related to [[Dmitri Nikolayevich Smirnov (footballer)|Dmitri Nikolayevich Smirnov]] with whom he played on the same team for several years for [[FC Moscow|FC Torpedo-ZIL Moscow]], [[FC Luch-Energiya Vladivostok|Luch]] and [[FC Tom Tomsk|Tom]]. To avoid confusion, he is usually referred to as '''Dmitri A. Smirnov''' or '''Smirnov I'''.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://news.sportbox.ru/Vidy_sporta/Futbol/stats/man_1111839708 Player page by sportbox.ru] {{dead link|date=April 2020}} {{in lang|ru}}\n* {{Sportbox.ru|Futbol/Smirnov-Dmitriy-Al-Futbol-13081980|Dmitry A. Smirnov}}\n* [http://www.luch-energy.ru/?team.main.players.08.pp-pl-luch-smirnov-24-07 Player page on the official Luch-Energiya website] {{in lang|ru}}\n* {{RPL player|Smirnov-Dmitriy|Dmitry A. Smirnov}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smirnov, Dmitry A.}}\n[[Category:Russian footballers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Moscow]]