le \u2013 citing result of on-going litigation between owner Chuck Brennan and his Dollar Loan Center operations, this after he was forced to shutter all of his businesses and assets following the South Dakota Division of Banking revoking the business licenses earlier this month. The move also came as a result of South Dakota voters having approved a measure in November 2016 capping high interest short-term loans at 36% interest.<ref>[https://radioinsight.com/headlines/119900/94-5-kbad-sioux-falls-goes-dark-owners-dollar-loan-business-becomes-illegal/ \u201c94.5 KBAD Sioux Falls Goes Dark As Owner\u2019s Dollar Loan Business Becomes Illegal\u201d] from Radio Insight (September 24, 2017)</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''October 1'''\n|''[[Car Talk]]'' ends distribution. The [[NPR]] series had been in reruns for five years following co-host [[Tom and Ray Magliozzi|Tom Magliozzi]]'s [[dementia]] diagnosis and eventual death.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/about-npr/487608540/nprs-best-of-car-talk-to-end-production-in-2017|title=NPR'S 'Best of Car Talk' to End Production in 2017|publisher=NPR.org|date=July 27, 2016}}</ref> \n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''November 17'''\n|After 19 years together, ''[[Mike & Mike]]'', [[ESPN Radio]]'s nationally broadcast morning show, ended its run. Host [[Mike Greenberg]] departed for ESPN television, while [[Mike Golic]], whose time in the time slot predated Greenberg's arrival, will continue with [[Trey Wingo]] as his co-host.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syracuse.com/axeman/index.ssf/2017/05/espn_announces_new_morning_shows_mike_and_mike_to_end_after_17_years.html|title=ESPN announces new shows; 'Mike and Mike' to end after 17 years|website=syracuse.com|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2|'''December 22'''\n|After a two-year run, ''The [[Ed Lover]] Show'' aired its final broadcast, with the final week's programs to be a best-of Show.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://radioinsight.com/headlines/121913/reach-media-cancels-ed-lover-show/|title=Reach Media Cancels Ed Lover Show|website=Radio Insight|accessdate=December 21, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Talk Radio Network]] abruptly ceases operations without notice.<ref>[https://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/172681/talk-radio-network-affiliates-left-in-dark-as-prog Talk Radio Network Affiliates Left In Dark as Programs Disappear From Satellite]</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=4|'''December 31'''\n|After a seven-year run, [[Nikki Sixx]] announced that he is ending his syndicated programs ''[[Sixx Sense with Nikki Sixx]]'' and the spinoffs ''Side Show Countdown'' and ''Side Show Classic'' to focus on other projects. [[Premiere Networks]], the shows' distributor, is expected to announce a replacement before the end of the year.<ref>[https://radioinsight.com/headlines/120345/nikki-sixx-exit-three-syndicated-shows-end-2017/ \"Nikki Sixx To Exit His Three Syndicated Shows At End Of 2017\"] from Radio Insight (October 12, 2017)</ref>\n|-\n|After 97 years, including a successful run as a Top 40 and the last 42 years with All-News, [[KQV]] [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania|Pittsburgh]] will sign off the air, citing a changing environment in news gathering and the deaths of its owners. It is not known at this point whether the license will return to the FCC or if a new buyer is being sought but station management has confirmed that they plan to air its last broadcast on this date regardless of the outcome.<ref>[http://www.post-gazette.com/local/city/2017/12/15/KQV-radio-going-off-the-air-Dec-31-all-news-format-Robert-W-Dickey-Jr/stories/201712150145 \u2033KQV going off the air at end of the year\u201d] from [[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]] (December 15, 2017)</ref>\n|-\n|Full service Oldies [[WSPQ]] [[Springville, New York]] ceased broadcasting on this date after 31 years, citing difficulties due to competition from the [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]] radio market in terms of revenue, its struggle to upgrade their facilities and the stigma of being a station that is privately owned.<ref>[http://www.springvillejournal.com/News/WSPQ-going-off-air-Jan-1.html \u201cWSPQ going off air Jan. 1\u201d] from Springville Journal (Springville, New York) (December 28, 2017)</ref>\n|-\n|[[WCAZ (Carthage, Illinois)|WCAZ]] [[Carthage, Illinois]] signs off. The station had been operating for months in defiance of an FCC order revoking its license.<ref>[http://www.wgem.com/story/37119033/2017/12/Thursday/carthage-radio-station-ordered-to-stop-operations \"Carthage Radio Station Ordered to Stop Operations\"] (wgem.com)</ref>\n|}\n\n==Deaths==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Name\n! Age\n! Notability <!--Include nationality-->\n! Source\n|-\n| February 15\n| [[Stuart McLean]]\n| 68\n| Canadian host of ''[[The Vinyl Cafe]]'' on [[CBC Radio]] and [[Public Radio International]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.nationalpost.com/arts/books/stuart-mclean-bestselling-author-and-host-of-cbc-radios-vinyl-cafe-has-died |title=Stuart McLean, bestselling author and host of CBC Radio's \u2019Vinyl Cafe,\u2019 has died |newspaper=[[National Post]] |date=February 15, 2017 |accessdate=February 15, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|February 20\n|[[Steve Hewlett (journalist)|Steve Hewlett]]\n|58\n|British host of ''[[The Media Show]]'' on [[BBC Radio 4]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-39027583|title=Broadcaster Steve Hewlett dies at 58|date=20 February 2017|publisher=|accessdate=28 October 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n|-\n|February 21\n|[[Frank Delaney]]\n|74\n|Irish-born author, creator and host of ''[[Word of Mouth (radio programme)|Word of Mouth]]'' on [[BBC Radio 4]]\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Obituary: Frank Delaney|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/life-and-style/people/obituary-frank-delaney-1.2987889|work=[[The Irish Times]]|location=Dublin|date=2017-02-25|accessdate=2019-11-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|February 22\n|[[Stephen Rhodes]]\n|66\n|British presenter on 