ul-hollingdale-dies/ First BBC Radio 2 host Paul Hollingdale dies] ''Radio Today'', July 6, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|July 9\n|Matt Patrick\n|58\n|American host on [[WKDD]] Akron and [[KTRH]] Houston\n|<ref>[https://ktrh.iheart.com/content/2017-07-09-matt-patrick-passes-away-after-lengthy-battle-with-cancer/#.WWKwC14K0sM.facebook Michael \u201cMatt\u201d Patrick Ryan passes away after lengthy cancer battle] iHeart Radio, July 9, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|July 16\n|Stephen Rice\n|46\n|American host on Austin, Texas stations [[KUT]] and [[KOOP (FM)|KOOP]], and gay rights activist\n|<ref>[http://www.statesman.com/news/local/radio-host-stephen-rice-dies-contributed-austin-lgbt-community/knPnHH0MblmpxbBLKtOtjI/ Radio host Stephen Rice dies; contributed to Austin\u2019s LGBT community] ''Austin Statesman'', July 16, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|July 23\n|Elliott Castro\n|68\n|Puerto Rican sports broadcaster and panelist of La Descarga Original on [[WSKN]] in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico]]\n|{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}\n|-\n|July 28\n|Pam Dixon\n|59\n|American radio personality in the [[Des Moines, Iowa|Des Moines]] market, notably as an on-air staffer with Saga Communications' [[KRNT (AM)|KRNT]], [[KIOA]] and [[KSTZ|KRNQ]]\n|<ref>[https://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/168112/pam-dixon-longtime-des-moines-radio-personality-di \"Pam Dixon, Longtime Des Moines Radio Personality, Dies At 59\"] from All Access (July 31, 2017)</ref>\n|-\n|August 1\n|Ismael Gonzalez\n|83\n|Puerto Rican radio host, entrepreneur and producer; known as \"El Loco de los Milagros\"\n|{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}\n|-\n|August 6\n|[[Darren Daulton]]\n|55\n|American retired professional baseball player ([[Philadelphia Phillies]], [[Florida Marlins]]) and host of \"Talking Baseball with Dutch\" on [[WPEN (FM)|WPEN]] in [[Burlington, New Jersey]] from 2010 to 2017\n|<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kelly|first1=Matt|title=Phillies legend Daulton passes away at 55: Wall of Fame catcher 'Dutch' battled brain cancer for 4 yea