ow''.\n|<ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hugh-hefner-dead-playboy-founder-sexual-trailblazer-was-91-708796 Hugh Hefner, Playboy Founder and Leader of '60s Sexual Revolution, Dies at 91] ''The Hollywood Reporter'', September 27, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|September 28\n|[[Alan Thompson (broadcaster)|Alan Thompson]]\n|54\n|British presenter on [[BBC Radio Wales]]\n|<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-41434703 BBC Radio Wales presenter Alan Thompson dies aged 54] BBC, September 28, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|September 30\n|[[Joe Taruc]]\n|70\n|Filipino news anchor and radio broadcaster ([[DZRH]], [[DZMM-AM]], [[DZBB-AM]])\n|<ref>[https://www.rappler.com/nation/183873-joe-taruc-dzrh-dies Veteran broadcaster Joe Taruc dies] ''Rappler'', September 30, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|October 10\n|[[Bob Schiller]]\n|98\n|American writer (''[[Duffy's Tavern]]'', ''[[Abbott and Costello#Radio|Abbott and Costello]]'', ''[[The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet#The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet radio show|The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet]]'', ''[[The Mel Blanc Show]]'', ''Sweeney and March'', and ''[[December Bride (radio program)|December Bride]]'')\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bob-schiller-dead-i-love-lucy-writer-was-98-1047459 |title=Bob Schiller, Writer on 'I Love Lucy,' Dies at 98 |date=2017-10-10 |accessdate=2017-10-10 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |author=Barnes, Mike}}</ref>\n|-\n|November 2\n|Bill Wilkerson\n|72\n|American news anchor and host ([[KMOX]] in [[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]]) and sports announcer ([[Missouri Tigers football]], [[History of the St. Louis Cardinals (NFL)|St. Louis Cardinals football]])\n|<ref>[https://www.stltoday.com/lifestyles/columns/joe-holleman/bill-wilkerson-longtime-radio-news-sports-announcer-dies-at/article_51e1b455-63c7-5e55-abe5-1637fd3f925e.html Bill Wilkerson, longtime radio news/sports announcer, dies at 72] ''St. Louis Post-Dispatch'', November 4, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|November 17\n|[[Robert D. Raiford]]\n|89\n|Ame