PN (AM)#WHN|WHN]], [[WMCA (AM)|WMCA]], and [[WEPN (AM)|WEVD]] in New York City; [[WEZE]] and [[WZLX]] in [[Boston]]; and [[WTNH|WNHC]] in [[New Haven, Connecticut]]. \n|<ref>[http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/02/23/alan-colmes-dies-66 Fox News Channel's Alan Colmes Dies at Age 66] Fox News Channel, February 23, 2017</ref> \n|-\n|March 3\n|[[Tommy Page]]\n|46\n|American singer/actor, VJ, record executive, publisher at ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', and VP/Executive at [[Pandora Radio]] and [[Cumulus Media]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7710182/tommy-page-ill-be-your-everything-singer-and-former-billboard-publisher-dies-at-46 |title=Tommy Page, Singer and Former Billboard Publisher, Dies 46 |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=2017-03-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|March 13\n|[[John Andariese]]\n|78\n|American sports journalist, reporter and analyst, nicknamed \"Johnny Hoops\" for his play-by-play of the [[New York Knicks]] broadcasts on TV and radio\n|<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/163649/new-york-knicks-radio-tv-analyst-john-andariese-di \"New York Knicks Radio, TV Analyst John Andariese Dies At 78\"] from All Access (March 14, 2017)</ref>\n|-\n|April 8\n|[[Brian Matthew]]\n|88\n|British presenter of ''[[Sounds of the 60s]]'' and several other shows on [[BBC Radio 2]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Obituary: Brian Matthew|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-39513249|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=2017-04-08|accessdate=2017-04-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|April 26\n|Larry Levite\n|77\n|American owner of [[WBEN (AM)|WBEN]] in [[Buffalo, New York]] from 1978 to 1994\n|<ref>[http://www.wkbw.com/news/larry-levite-publisher-and-ceo-of-buffalo-spree-passes-away Larry Levite, publisher and CEO of Buffalo Spree, passes away] WKBW, April 26, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|May 19\n|[[Wayne Walker]]\n|80\n|Retired American football player ([[Detroit Lions]]). Also former radio color commentator for the [[San Francisco 49ers]] and [[Oakland Athletic