-legend-gary-ocallaghan-passes-away-aged-83/news-story Radio legend Gary O\u2019Callaghan passes away aged 83] ''The Daily Telegraph'', August 18, 2017</ref>\n|-\n|August 19\n|[[Dick Gregory]]\n|84\n|American comedian, actor, author, and activist; radio work included morning host at [[WOL (AM)|WOL]] Washington, D.C., ''Make It Plain'' on [[SiriusXM]] 146, and ''[[Imus in the Morning]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/local/obituaries/la-me-dick-gregory-20170819-story.html|title=Dick Gregory, who rose from poverty to become a groundbreaking comedian and civil rights activist, dies at 84|author=Dennis McLellahn|work=[[The Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=August 19, 2017|date=August 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/dick-gregory-dead-stand-up-comedy-legend-civil-rights-activist-was-84-1004479|title=Dick Gregory, Trailblazer of Stand-Up Comedy, Dies at 84|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=August 19, 2017|date=August 19, 2017|author=Mike Barnes}}</ref>\n|-\n|August 20\n|[[Jerry Lewis]]\n|91\n|American actor and comedian (co-star of ''[[The Martin and Lewis Show]]'' on the [[NBC Red Network|NBC Radio Network]] from 1949 to 1953, alongside [[Dean Martin]])\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/jerry-lewis-dies-dead-nutty-professor-1202533899/|title=Jerry Lewis, Comedy Legend, Dies at 91|last=Dagan|first=Richard Natale, Carmel|date=2017-08-20|work=Variety|access-date=2017-08-20|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|August 21\n|[[Felo Ram\u00edrez]]\n|94\n|Cuban-American sportscaster, most notably for the Spanish language play-by-play broadcasts of the [[Miami Marlins]] from 1993 to 2017 for which he received the [[Ford C. Frick Award]]. Also appeared on the Spanish version of the ''[[Gillette Cavalcade of Sports]]'' on the [[NBC Red Network|NBC Radio Network]]. \n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/20417119/hall-fame-broadcaster-rafael-felo-ramirez-dies-94|title=Legendary broadcast